pickleBerry is a shell-based, TUI file manager designed for efficient keyboard-driven file operations. It provides a lightweight alternative to traditional graphical file managers, offering dynamic keybindings and essential file management features within a terminal interface. It requires familiarity with basic shell commands and relies on dependencies like bash, fzf, and tput.

Mousemaster enables users to control their mouse cursor using only a keyboard, offering an alternative to traditional mouse input. It provides multiple navigation modes, including normal, hint, grid, and screen selection, all of which are fully customizable. This tool aims to enhance accessibility and productivity by providing a mouseless experience.

Scraperr is a self-hosted web scraping solution that allows users to extract data from websites using XPath selectors. It provides a user-friendly interface for managing scraping jobs, visualizing results, and exporting data in various formats. Key features include XPath-based extraction, queue management, domain spidering, and media downloads.

StegCloak is a JavaScript steganography tool that hides secrets within text by compressing, encrypting, and cloaking them with invisible Unicode characters. It offers password protection, integrity checks, and high-speed performance, making it suitable for various applications like watermarking, covert communication, and data exfiltration via text.

The fingerprint-suite repository provides tools for generating and injecting browser fingerprints to anonymize web scrapers. It includes modules for generating realistic HTTP headers and browser fingerprints, injecting these fingerprints into Playwright or Puppeteer instances, and a Bayesian network implementation for fingerprint generation.
